channel.title: mycatalog updates
channel.description: 'My Catalog' uses the IBM Cloud catalog API to retrieve data from the catalog. It attempts to be as accurate as possible. This feed shows additions, updates, removals from the catalog. Use with care. It is a work-in-progress :)

item.title: [updated] Databases for MongoDB (databases-for-mongodb) has a new plan named enterprise-sharding
item.description: One highly available MongoDB Enterprise Sharding Server instance with three data members. The Enterprise plan is priced based on disk storage, RAM, and backup storage allocated to deployments, prorated hourly. Databases for MongoDB instances have a minimum of 20GB of Disk and 14GB of RAM, and 6 cores per data member.
